.TH "estimate_pid_constants" 9 "estimate_pid_constants" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
estimate_pid_constants \- Estimate the constants for the PID controller
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" estimate_pid_constants
.BI "(struct thermal_zone_device *tz "  ","
.BI "u32 sustainable_power "  ","
.BI "int trip_switch_on "  ","
.BI "int control_temp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "tz" 12
thermal zone for which to estimate the constants
.IP "sustainable_power" 12
sustainable power for the thermal zone
.IP "trip_switch_on" 12
trip point number for the switch on temperature
.IP "control_temp" 12
target temperature for the power allocator governor
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is used to update the estimation of the PID
controller constants in struct thermal_zone_parameters.
